[{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1776580702.0,"description":"Always had been a xfce DE kind of guy but wanted to have the nice features of Fedora so wanted to give it a try and the cute little graphics helped me understand what all the dash/panel/workspace stuff is all about.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":672199,"score":33,"summary":"Helped me get started with GNOME","user_display":"Kier","user_hash":"23c57fab099e0a307bd9fb4a43c0399b93bec296","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"48.1"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1765874871.0,"description":"Such a very welcoming tour guide for Gnome DEs","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":663077,"score":0,"summary":"Simple tour as should be!","user_display":"Genjie Ching","user_hash":"feaa3261f0417f9307384d4cf1229a1b08a34de0","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"48.1"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1759382725.0,"description":"Could be nice to have more details.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":60,"reported":0,"review_id":657413,"score":0,"summary":"Basic Tour","user_display":"Ahren Dosanjh","user_hash":"ae9f90b75f47023bb6b7e8617998716a235d759b","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"48.1"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1758753855.0,"description":"Not bad, but not really that useful either. There is so mch potential here. This app could be used not only for introducing users to Gnome Desktop as installed, but could also be a central location for brief documentation on how the DE works, and be updated to show whats new as features drop (think something like the My Pixel app).","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":80,"reported":0,"review_id":656943,"score":0,"summary":"It's OK I guess","user_display":"JB","user_hash":"f73f55a02fd31dfe12a9747591653a0d220cfa00","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"48.1"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1754422806.0,"description":"I cannot uninstall this product","distro":"Endless OS","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":20,"reported":0,"review_id":653655,"score":0,"summary":"Do not want","user_display":"Tyler","user_hash":"978e7ce3a0c204537e0f2646113bd7e9926d18d9","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"unknown"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1737044895.0,"description":"People say \"there are not enough tips\" -- but, in reality, would anyone ever want to go through, like, 50 screens of them? Hell no! The user would 100% close it without even thinking.\n\nAlthough, I feed the text descriptions on each slide should be more verbose, detailed, and feature more concrete examples -- for example, the first slide does not explain where to find the apps, only saying there are somewhere in the overview -- and how do I know I need to press the rightmost button if I never used GNOME or even a computer before?","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":80,"reported":0,"review_id":640232,"score":0,"summary":"Good app","user_display":null,"user_hash":"3ae427a92743048166628330698a081c867d5793","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"47.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1734688025.0,"description":"Help my mom told me this is a virus\n\n\ni have candy","distro":"CentOS Stream","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":20,"reported":0,"review_id":638431,"score":0,"summary":"My mom told me this is a virus","user_display":"Burke","user_hash":"36bae207be7ac14107a063daafa2f192c4e1af44","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"46.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1727388354.0,"description":"Functions well, pleasent ui, welcoming\npamphlet. wouldn't call it a guide nor a tour. \nDoesn't seem necessary unless additional information is added.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":60,"reported":0,"review_id":633231,"score":0,"summary":"Missed potential","user_display":"unhome","user_hash":"136166913ec05942317216c5b66015fc3894b1ef","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"45.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1719903901.0,"description":"Danke, danke. I feel so sigma. It ACTUALLY WORKED!","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_AU.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":626594,"score":0,"summary":"Uninstall WORKED on Fedora!","user_display":"Max Parry","user_hash":"ed4cf5d517017273974a2f1bbd676b6efb62df80","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"46.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1714208957.0,"description":"Gnome 46 is great, I love it, but this \"tour\" , is doesn't tackle anything helpful\n\nI believe this is the right path, having a tour app for newcomers, but it just isn't helpful. I hope this gets more tips in the future","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":60,"reported":0,"review_id":620968,"score":0,"summary":"Not helpful, but it's the right idea","user_display":"shaytan","user_hash":"b67fe4c22914efc728f9788cc79cdbda6f90cdbe","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"46.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1713197842.0,"description":"Can't uninstall","distro":"Arch Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":40,"reported":0,"review_id":619981,"score":0,"summary":"Nice for a first look","user_display":null,"user_hash":"21adc970c659119893ee416427b1c1df7c065ad6","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"unknown"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1700370918.0,"description":"gnome is incredibly simplistic in it's design and does not need a tour on all of its individual quirks and features. this tour tells you the most important information that you need to navigate the desktop environment without overloading you all at once with info that you may not even be interested in. \nThe tour does not ask you for much of your time, which I think is the most valueable feature of it.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":607094,"score":0,"summary":"GNOME does not need a complicated tour","user_display":"im-vegan-btw","user_hash":"2c3d328f57a68f1042cd3615466c342acda45e9b","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"45.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1694272520.0,"description":"amazing and nice","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":601128,"score":0,"summary":"cool","user_display":"Dev","user_hash":"ff9b2625952df31b5ca732407225e8738dc95778","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"44.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1693889100.0,"description":"All this app does is show a few slides with VERY minimal instructive text. It doesn't actually give you a tour of anything. It basically says \"Welcome to gnome, you can search for stuff. Good luck.\" Either cut this or make it an actual introduction/tour. As it is there's no reason at all for it to be a standalone application. Or to exist.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":20,"reported":0,"review_id":600751,"score":0,"summary":"Useless","user_display":"matt","user_hash":"33329ecff53b4e61f1c30e9388758ff15e6f6765","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"44.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1686132119.0,"description":"Would like to remove it from Silverblue. May keep it if in future there was a more comprehensive quick start guide i.e. tells you about things without actually showing you how. At present state this app is pretty much useless.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_NZ.UTF-8","rating":40,"reported":0,"review_id":593176,"score":0,"summary":"Too vague","user_display":null,"user_hash":"fcb30155b8ce63990736515edda703b676cdf648","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"44.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1682530201.0,"description":"This is good application for beginners like me","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":584394,"score":0,"summary":"This is good application for beginners like me","user_display":"Dmytro","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"44.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1663870492.0,"description":"With this being the first thing I saw when I booted up my Fedora install for the first time, I knew I loved Gnome before I even used it!","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":100,"reported":0,"review_id":521866,"score":0,"summary":"Made Me Fall in Love","user_display":"Brandon Boese","user_hash":"beca7f31e214e5566a4d70ec3c2242d9218ef7ff","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"42.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1659457971.0,"description":"It only shows basic trackpad gestures and how to get around GNOME. I would like it more if it had some default keyboard shortcuts listed as well.","distro":"Fedora Linux","karma_down":0,"karma_up":0,"locale":"en_US.UTF-8","rating":80,"reported":0,"review_id":507112,"score":0,"summary":"Very minimal tour","user_display":"Raspberry","user_hash":"775ce7ab480910852d0d6e586e067b151fe26999","user_skey":"7e15e58aa11a9c1e5bdef47f6ea83aaa4b3308ec","version":"42.0"},{"app_id":"org.gnome.Tour","date_created":1658611160.0,"description":"